---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="AcuLens — AI Copilot for Field Service Technicians"
  description="AcuLens is an AI copilot on Meta smart glasses for HVAC, plumbing, and electrical technicians. Real-time diagnostics, hands-free repair walkthroughs, Acumatica Field Service integration."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="aculens-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="aculens-badge">In development with design partners</div>
      <h1>Your ERP just got eyes on the job.<br/><em>Your tech just got his hands back.</em></h1>
      <p>AcuLens is an AI copilot built for Meta smart glasses — giving field service technicians real-time diagnostics, hands-free repair guidance, and automatic Acumatica work order updates without touching a screen.</p>
      <a href="mailto:steve@acumaveninc.com?subject=AcuLens Early Access" class="btn-access">Request Early Access →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Value Props -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What AcuLens Does</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Three problems field service companies deal with every day — solved without asking your tech to use another app.</p>
      <div class="aculens-props">
        <div class="aculens-prop">
          <div class="prop-icon">🔍</div>
          <h3>Real-Time Diagnostics</h3>
          <p>The AI sees what your tech sees — through Meta smart glasses. It identifies equipment, analyzes symptoms, and surfaces the most likely causes and fixes in real time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="aculens-prop">
          <div class="prop-icon">📋</div>
          <h3>Auto Work Orders</h3>
          <p>Observations, parts used, and repair steps are automatically captured and synced to Acumatica Field Service — no paperwork, no double-entry, no end-of-day data dump.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="aculens-prop">
          <div class="prop-icon">🙌</div>
          <h3>Hands-Free Operation</h3>
          <p>Voice-controlled. Screen-free. The tech stays focused on the job while AcuLens handles the documentation and lookup. No tablet balancing act in a cramped equipment room.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Trades callout -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="aculens-trades">
        <h3>Built for HVAC, Plumbing &amp; Electrical</h3>
        <p>AcuLens is purpose-built for the trades — not a generic AI tool bolted onto a glasses SDK. The diagnostic models, integration points, and workflow design are built around how technicians actually work in the field.</p>
        <div class="trade-list">
          <span class="trade-item">🌡️ HVAC</span>
          <span class="trade-item">🔧 Plumbing</span>
          <span class="trade-item">⚡ Electrical</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How it fits Acumatica -->
  <section style="background: var(--light);">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Acumatica Field Service, Connected</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">AcuLens is designed by an Acumatica specialist — which means the integration isn't an afterthought.</p>
      <div class="services-grid">
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>📡 Live field data</h3>
          <p>Pulls open work orders, equipment history, and service agreements from Acumatica so your tech has context before they arrive.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>🔄 Automatic sync</h3>
          <p>Work order updates, time entries, and parts consumption write back to Acumatica Field Service automatically — as the job progresses.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>📊 Management visibility</h3>
          <p>Dispatchers and service managers see real-time job status in Acumatica without chasing tech status calls.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Early Access CTA -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="aculens-signup">
        <h2>Get Early Access</h2>
        <p>AcuLens is in active development with a small group of field service companies. If you run HVAC, plumbing, or electrical operations and want to be part of the design partner program, reach out.</p>
        <a href="mailto:steve@acumaveninc.com?subject=AcuLens Early Access" class="btn-access">Request Early Access →</a>
        <p style="margin-top: 1.25rem; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">No commitment. We're looking for companies who want to shape the product, not just buy it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer bridge -->
  <section style="text-align: center; padding: 2rem 0 3rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem;">AcuLens is a product of <a href="/">AcuMaven Inc</a> — Steve Milner's Acumatica consulting practice.<br/>Questions? <a href="mailto:steve@acumaveninc.com">steve@acumaveninc.com</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
